Darkheart
data.notes: 墨 doesn't have an intrinsic meaning, but it is commonly paired with 水 which would make 墨水 which is 'ink'. So many people will think of ink, so 'inkheart' is not a horrible translation, but as a concept, 墨 is generally associated with darkness, so 'darkheart' is perhaps a better translation? There could also be a relationship with getting too close to darkness, or it could just be someone trying to be cool.
